  • Method Details

    • openCSV

      java.lang.String openCSV​(java.lang.String fileName, boolean embeddedLabels, java.lang.String delimiter, int timeStampIndex) throws java.io.IOException, DatasetFileOpenException
      Method that opens dataset based on parameters provided by user. On failure the dataset should be empty, even if it had data prior to calling this method.
      Parameters:
      fileName - dataset file name
      embeddedLabels - true if first row of the dataset contains field names
      delimiter - delimiter in the CSV file
      timeStampIndex - index of field containing timestamps
      Returns:
      String with message after successfully opening specified dataset
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - if fails to read the dataset file
      DatasetFileOpenException - if file contains improper dataset or wrong arguments were passed

    • isOpen

      boolean isOpen()

    • getFieldNames

      java.util.Vector<java.lang.String> getFieldNames() throws DataSetNotOpenedException
      Getter of all dataset field names.
      Returns:
      Vector of field names.
      Throws:
      DataSetNotOpenedException - When user tries to access dataset that is not opened.

    • getFieldCopy

      java.util.Vector<java.lang.Double> getFieldCopy​(java.lang.String fieldName) throws NoFieldFoundException, DataSetNotOpenedException
      Method that creates opy of all values in a numeric field.
      Parameters:
      fieldName - Name of the field.
      Returns:
      Vector containing field values.
      Throws:
      NoFieldFoundException - When user passes invalid fieldName
      DataSetNotOpenedException - When user tries to access dataset that is not opened.

    • getTimeStampsCopy

      java.util.Vector<java.time.Instant> getTimeStampsCopy() throws DataSetNotOpenedException
      Method that returns copy of timestamp field.
      Returns:
      Vector containing all timestamps from timestamp field.
      Throws:
      DataSetNotOpenedException - When user tries to access dataset that is not opened.
